Light was seen as she neared the end of a shaft. Padding along at a decent 
pace. 

At the opening of the shaft, glancing about outside to see a very different 
Cyberton that what she was used to.. from what she remembered. 

&quot;No,&quot; she whispered. A pain in her voice. It wasn&#39;t that familiar 
metallic/robotic voice that was so familiar to her, but such a plain, 
ordinary organic like voice. 

A curiousity sprung up within her. She wanted to see if any part of Cybertron 
remained as it was. Or was it all a mix of this organic & cybernetic? 

******************************

Padding along in the shadows & alleys, much like Ravage once did. Her optics 
glanced about, taking in this new Cybertron, much to her grief & distaste. 

It pained her. & surely enough, it would have pained any Decepticon. Even 
worse, she was disgraced for being reformated into this organic like body. 

Sad & lonely, for the first time in her existance, her thoughts went to her 
past. Thinking about the days of the Great War, the Decepticons. The battles 
with the Autobots, Cybertron as it once was. Energon. Her rivals with 
Elita-1. 

Megatron. She felt so ashamed. If he were functioning & standing before her, 
she would beg him to either return her to her former body or help her to 
permenantly cease to function.  

As she moved through the alleys & shadows of the streets of Cybertron, 
Megatron&#39;s faceplate remained the dominant figure in her mind. If she could 
see him again, she would be reassured. 



